properties.Title: Rainfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A long episode of rain, at times heavy, continues. A further 10 to 20 mm of rain is expected to fall tonight over the B.C. Peace River, Fort Nelson, and Muncho Lake Park - Stone Mountain Park regions. A persistent low pressure system over Alberta has led to several days of heavy rain over the B.C. Peace River, Fort Nelson, and Muncho Lake Park- Stone Mountain Park regions. So far in this rain event, 50 to 80 mm of rain has fallen over the region since Wednesday morning. The showers are expected to ease on Saturday as the low pressure system weakens. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather in British Columbia or Yukon, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm or #YTStorm.
